Pio Pio is an authentic Peruvian restaurant in NY city known for its Peruvian style rotisserie chicken. The ambience is very unique with a design precisely based on canes. It is an excellent restaurant to celebrate your birthday because of the unique song they play for the celebrations. The food has some similarity with Inidan, Thai and Chinese cuisine making it popular to people from such countries. The service and food quality is way above average. Try to get a table inside so as to enjoy the ambience. The Pio Pio chicken is a must try which is basically chicken leg pieces marinated in a mixture of cumin, garlic and some Peruvian spices and it comes with a side of green sauce made of coriander, green chilly and onion paste
